 :tx/rationale "Create task: PERF-4: Session daemon with Unix socket. Long-running process that keeps the store hot in memory, accepts commands via Unix socket (.braid/daemon.sock), processes transactions incrementally, computes F(S)/StatusSnapshot lazily on mutation. APPROACH: (1) braid daemon start: fork background process, bind .braid/daemon.sock. (2) Store loaded once at startup, held in memory. (3) On new txn file (inotify/kqueue watch on .braid/txns/): parse and append incrementally. (4) On status request: return pre-computed snapshot (updated lazily after mutations). (5) braid status detects running daemon and connects via socket instead of loading store. (6) Graceful degradation: if daemon not running, fall back to PERF-1/2/3 cache path. (7) braid daemon stop: clean shutdown, write final cache. ACCEPTANCE: (A) braid status with daemon: <50ms. (B) braid status without daemon: falls back to cache (<1s). (C) Daemon handles concurrent clients (multiple agents). (D) Daemon survives agent crash (no leaked locks). (E) PID file prevents double-start. DEPENDS-ON: PERF-3. FILE: crates/braid/src/daemon.rs (new) + crates/braid/src/commands/mod.rs"
